When inserting a JIRA issue link in Confluence, the new styling in Confluence 5 makes it very difficult to see the difference between selected and not-selected issues in the list.

On my particular monitor there was barely any difference between the light-blue background of the selected row and the white background of the unselected rows. I strongly suspect that the small difference in contrast would be difficult for some partially-sighted users to discern as well.

I would suggest making the blue a bit darker, or having a more obvious indicator of which row is selected such as an arrow at the start of the row...

