It would be nice to have an option to make Confluence directly connect to a database, in order to bypass SSO problems.

We're using Siteminder from CA as our enterprise SSO solution, which isn't supported by Atlassian. And because the Siteminder wants the Confluence server to authenticate via it's own login, Confluence is not able to authenticate itself against JIRA, which makes it impossible to use the JIRA Macro in Confluence.

There's only way I can think of to bypass the SSO, which is, creating a DB-connection from Confluence to the JIRA-DB and executing the SELECT queries directly on the database.

