I'd like to see a configurable warning displayed on the login screen if you are using an old browser. Default to something like "Please upgrade your browser or prepare yourself for greatly reduced user experience and possible loss of functionality... Muhhahaha!". See functionality provided by the jReject jQuery plugin project (there are no doubt lots of these kinds of plugins for jQuery).

For public wikis, it probably makes more sense to have a banner, like you see on github.com when you visit it using IE version less than 9. Actually, I like the fact they include the note about turning off compatibility mode. One improvement I'd like to see over the github solution is to allow the user to ignore the message for the remaining duration of the session (as supported by jReject).

